thread.title_full: Staff predictions for Rutgers-Michigan State: Do the Scarlet Knights have a chance? | NJ.com

author: Dan Duggan | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: Staff predictions for Michigan State: Do the Scarlet Knights have a chance?
text:
PISCATAWAY â€” The stars are aligned for Rutgers to upset Michigan State on Saturday night.
The Scarlet Knights are coming off a bye, they'll be in front of a raucous "blackout" crowd for a prime-time matchup, star receiver Leonte Carroo has been reinstated from his suspension and the banged up Spartans looked vulnerable in a 24-21 win over Purdue last week.
So, did any of the NJ.com writers pick the 13.5-point underdog Scarlet Knights to pull off the upset? Umm, no. Accuse us of negativity, but Steve Politi and I have correctly predicted the outcomes of Rutgers ' first four games.
Everyone nailed their prediction of a Scarlet Knights win in their last game against Kansas. Of the 972 fan votes on NJ.com, 80 percent predicted a Rutgers victory .
Here are our predictions for the Michigan State game:
Dan Duggan: Despite all of the reasons for optimism listed above, I'm not convinced Rutgers can compete with a high-level Big Ten opponent. And despite all of the hand-wringing over Michigan State's relatively slim margin of victory during its 5-0 start, the Spartans return many of the key pieces from last season's 45-3 win over Rutgers . I expect Michigan State's defensive line to dominate and the offense to click in a lopsided win.
Duggan's Prediction: Michigan State 38, Rutgers 13
